examples.en: Her long skirt brushed the floor.
He brushed the fluff off his coat.
Nell brushed past him in the doorway.
Her hair was brushed back from her face.
He brushed aside criticisms of his performance.
Charlotte brushed against him as she left the room.
The cow brushed away the flies with a whisk of its tail.
She brushed the suit before hanging it back into the closet.
She brushed her hair and piled it carefully on top of her head.
He reached out and brushed a strand of hair away from her face.
The committee brushed off his enquiries with their usual "It's under control, don't worry".
Ella brushed the crumbs off her jacket.
